unwound.title: Welcome! You are invited to join a webinar: Food Literacy Opportunities for Children and Youth While Schools are Closed. After registering, you will receive a confirmation email about joining the webinar.
unwound.description: In this unprecedented time of school closures, how are schools and organizations across Ontario providing food literacy education for children and youth? Join this webinar, organized by Sustain Ontario's Edible Education Network, to hear from our speakers and brainstorm with other participants about how to support remote food literacy education for elementary and secondary students. This event will be structured as a conversation where our speakers will share their stories, after which other participants will be invited to ask questions and to share their ideas and activities for providing remote food literacy education during this time. Speakers: - Rav Sing / Merissa Nudelman, Ecosource (Mississauga) - Derek Brez, Sir Guy Carleton Secondary School (Ottawa) - Anne Munier / Brenda Moore, Loving Spoonful (Kingston) - Danielle Findlay, OSNP Windsor-Essex - Brooke Ziebell, FoodShare Toronto

unwound.description: Public health scientists predict that school closures due to the COVID-19 pandemic will exacerbate the epidemic of childhood obesity in the United States. unwound.title: Welcome! You are invited to join a webinar: Food Literacy Opportunities for Children and Youth While Schools are Closed. After registering, you will receive a confirmation email about joining the webinar.
unwound.description: In this unprecedented time of school closures, how are schools and organizations across Ontario providing food literacy education for children and youth? Join this webinar, organized by Sustain Ontario's Edible Education Network, to hear from our speakers and brainstorm with other participants about how to support remote food literacy education for elementary and secondary students. This event will be structured as a conversation where our speakers will share their stories, after which other participants will be invited to ask questions and to share their ideas and activities for providing remote food literacy education during this time. Speakers: - Rav Sing / Merissa Nudelman, Ecosource (Mississauga) - Derek Brez, Sir Guy Carleton Secondary School (Ottawa) - Anne Munier / Brenda Moore, Loving Spoonful (Kingston) - Danielle Findlay, OSNP Windsor-Essex - Brooke Ziebell, FoodShare Toronto
